As the comments already points out, there is nothing wrong about the format name. The actual format is really called &quot;JPEG&quot;, short for [&quot;Joint Photographic Experts Group&quot;](https://jpeg.org/about.html). The reason `.jpg` or `.JPG` is typically used for file extension, is due to the fact that arcane file systems only allowed 3 letter file extensions. 

If, on the other hand, what you really want to know is the file extension, use a `File` object, and extract the part of the file name after the dot. Using `ImageIO` is way overkill for such a task. 

```java
File file = new File(...); 

String fileName = file.getName();
int index = fileName.lastIndexOf(&#39;.&#39;);

if (index &gt;= 0) {
    return fileName.substring(index + 1);
}

// No period found
return null;
```

